codex
Changed `content/papers/random.md` with minimal structural QA edits only.

Summary of changes:
- Fixed markdown table formatting in the `NEWSPEAK` section by converting the malformed centered table block to a standard Markdown table.
- Added missing blank-line paragraph boundaries in multiple places where prose paragraphs were unintentionally merged.
- Normalized the lone equation-reference chain:
  - changed display equation tag from `\tag{\dag}` to `\tag{1}`
  - updated in-text references `()` to `(1)` (`integral`, `method`, and `joint distribution` mentions).
- Removed non-body trailing metadata lines:
  - `Dept. of Physics`
  - `Washington University`
  - `St. Louis, Missouri 63130`
  - `U.S.A.`
- Kept the footnote citation formatting intact and attached the `[^1]` marker to the sentence (instead of leaving it on a standalone line).
- Replaced two ambiguous in-body numeric equation mentions tied to external discussion so there are no unresolved local display-equation references.

Self-check completed:
- Paragraph breaks intended as paragraph boundaries are now blank-line separated.
- No unresolved local in-text equation references to missing display-equation numbers remain.
